<font color="#FF0000">HEALING OURSELVES</font><br>
<tt>Sun Aug 17 20:41:43 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
SparrowHawk,<br><br>
I have had the opportunity to talk to some of the family of the Chinese who fought the Vietnamese after we officially left.  They feel a great deal like we do.<br><br>
They fought valiantly, but ultimately were betrayed by their less than trustworthy Communist Regime.  It is interesting that conversations in the last few years with sons or family of some these warriors show they didn't care much for the treatment from their own government.  They care even less for the Vietnamese.<br><br>
A country run by feudal warlords and thugs using their people as cannon fodder.  No respect for us or those who helped them.  Wild animals can bite the hand who feeds them.  Some things never change.<br><br>

<p><code>--   (Silent Warrior) </code><p>


